contact_name: Directorate-General for Communications Networks, Content and Technology

resources.description: Microdata file of the survey. 1753 rows for each of the hospitals and around 250 columns for the variables extracted from the questionnaire.
Codification manual, providing labels for each of the variables and explanation of the codification conventions.

resources.name: Final report of the study presenting main results of the survey.
Methodological report (census of acute hospitals, sampling, questionnaire, comparison with previous surveys)
Web page of the researchers that have conducted the study/survey.

description: Raw data of a survey on around 1800 acute hospitals to measure the level of deployment and take-up of ICT and eHealth applications. Coverage of EU28 Member States plus Iceland and Norvay. Interview realised during winter 2012/2013. A previous data collection was conducted in automn 2010 under DG INFSO SMART study 2009/022.
title: European Hospital Survey Benchmarking Deployment of eHealth services (2012-13 update)
